DOCUMENT();

#image scale
$imgScale = .2;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*2745;
$height = $imgScale*1001;

loadMacros(   
	"PGstandard.pl",     # Standard macros for PG language
	"MathObjects.pl",
	"PGML.pl",
	"parserPopUp.pl",
	"parserMultiAnswer.pl",
	"parserRadioButtons.pl",
	#"source.pl",        # allows code to be displayed on certain sites.
	#"PGcourse.pl", 	 # Customization file for the course
   	);

TEXT(beginproblem());

##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

Context("Numeric");
#given
$V1= random(0.5,1,0.1); #[m/s]
$W= random(1,2,0.1); #[m]

#computation
$Ans= 998*2*$W*$V1**2*(1/(1-sin(50*pi/180))-1);# [N]

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.05,);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-FLU-18-068.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

The vertical gate in a water channel is partially open, as in the figure. Assuming no change in water level and a hydrostatic pressure distribution, Find the streamwise force, [`F_x`], on one-half of the gate for water at [`20^{\circ}C`], [`V_1 = [$V1]`] [`m/s`], [`h = 2`] [`m`], [`w = [$W]`] [`m`], and [`\theta = 50^{\circ}`]. 

[`F_x=`] [____]{"$Ans"} [`N`]

END_PGML

